AGI - Two twenty years were arrested by the police and transferred to prison for the robbery in the street committed on January 31 to the founder of the theater Franco Parenti Andree Ruth Shammah. That evening the director, after dinner, had walked on his own to reach Piazza Cordusio and take a taxi to return home but, while walking via Bocchetto, suddenly, two men arrived. One of them had taken it briefly for the neck and, immediately after, with a sudden gesture, had torn the necklace from 1,500 euros. The gesture, however, was so impetuous that Ruth Shammah had lost his balance by finishing on the hood of a car> parked.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
From the surveillance camera analysis, mobile team cops have collected clues to identify the two 20-year-olds, such as, in particular, a showy tattoo on the neck by one of the two robbers. Investigators of the crimes section against the heritage, coordinated by the proxy, thanks to analytical research on data banks, managed to identify a person with physical characteristics similar to those of the boy with tattoo on the neck.
&nbsp;
Further investigations have finally revealed that the suspect together with a compatriot, had been arrested the same evening by the Carabinieri of the Company Cathedral for another robbery. The comparison of the images with the arrested subjects has escaped any doubt: not only one of the two authors of the second robbery had as a distinctive sign a tattoo on the neck but, moreover, both wore the same clothing immortalized by the cameras> that had recorded the robbery to the damage of the director.&nbsp;
