AGI - The AGI Editorial Assembly met yesterday on the second day of the strike proclaimed in light of news on the possible sale of the agency. The Assembly has taken note with great satisfaction of the numerous testimonies of solidarity received in these hours and of the media attention that the story is also raising internationally. In the assembly the mayoral representative of the AGI polygraphs expressed the great concern of the political colleagues for the unknown about their future in case of sale of the agency.
&nbsp;
The Assembly thanked the CoR for the great effort and for the excellent work done in setting up the protest initiatives that are having a great echo. Waiting for the Board to meet the Company and the Management, the Assembly unanimously confirms the state of agitation to which from today, Saturday 23 March, the withdrawal of signatures from the news and the site is added. The further three days of strike of the package approved last Monday remain at the disposal of the Board. At the beginning of the next week will be convened a new assembly to which the leaders of the Fnsi will be invited.

