AGI - Approximately 300 people gathered tonight in Cagliari, in Piazza Garibaldi, for a demonstration of solidarity in Ilaria Salis, the teacher and anti-fascist militant, held for over a year in a maximum security prison in Budapest, Hungary, pending judgment. The event is attended by his father Roberto, who attended the classic Siotto high school in Sardinia.> Promotor was the Committee 'From Cagliari to Ilaria Salis', composed of a group of citizens of Cagliari and Sardinia, in collaboration with about forty associations and trade union movements, including the Cgil, with the Sardinian general secretary Fausto Durante, and the trade union Confederation Sarda, with Giacomo Meloni. Also present is the secretary of the Sardinian Pd, Piero Comandini, as well as former high schoolmates of Roberto Salis.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<em> Roberta Secci v AGI&nbsp;</em>
&nbsp;
"We are convinced that even here in Sardinia it is necessary to make the voice of solidarity and support for the struggle of Ilaria and its family for the respect of its rights," he explained, on the eve of the presidio, Pietro Pani, referent of the Organizing Committee who intends to keep the attention on the case. "We are all and all Ilaria Salis>," the protesters said. On 28 March next in Budapest, the next hearing of the trial was set, in which the teacher was accused of participating in the clashes of 10 February 2023 in the Hungarian capital with the European neo-Nazis on the eve of the "Tag der Ehre", the Day of Remembrance. She is challenged to have attacked, together with other demonstrators, two Neonazi participants, who had reported minor injuries. Ilaria Salis declared herself innocent. The defence will present an application for house arrests in Hungary. So far a similar request has been submitted three times, but for domiciles in Italy.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
< blockquote
"Ilaria will be happy, I will show you the photos of this beautiful event for her"
</blockquote
&nbsp;
Roberto Salis, father of the teacher and anti-fascist military held in Budapest and for over a year waiting for judgment thanked the many shortcomings tonight in Cagliari to support him and his daughter and ask for his release. Next to him, a former professor and former comrades in Section E of High School Siotto. "Any of the majority of center-rights in Italy claims that it must be my daughter to prove her innocence, which is not how it works. It is the accusation that must prove that someone is guilty."
&nbsp;
"Hungary is a nation in which there is a social system that is defined as ethnic nationalism," Salis said after retracing the time of arrest and the hard weeks of prison told by Ilaria in a letter of 18 pages delivered to his lawyer. In his words also a condemnation of the neo-Nazi demonstration that his daughter had gone to contest in February 2023 in Budapest. "Orban took power in a democratic way, of course," said Roberto Salis. "Here we continue to say that where there is an election then everything is fine: These are democratic because they have made elections, as has happened in Russia recently. But if someone takes power with a democratic election, then he can't do the tyrant, because if he does the tyrant, there is no democratic nation. Hitler also took power with a democratic election then did we have Nazism."
